The paper deals with the complexity of Graph Isomorphism on graphs that exclude a fixed graph as an induced minor. This topic is closely related to graph theory and combinatorics, which are covered by the cs.DM and cs.DS sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the study of clique-width, which is a measure of the complexity of graphs and is covered by the cs.CC sub-category. The paper also involves the use of algorithms and computational complexity theory, which are covered by the cs.CG and cs.GT sub-categories.
